message: For the benefit of you guys. Kamada found a patient yesterday on a home visit with a very bad infection of the leg. The patient was going to stay at home but we advised them to go to Mukono District Health Center 4 in town and be seen by the doctors. This is important as the infection was very bad and the woman could die if this spread to the bone. Some were worried about the doctors wanting to ask for money. Remember that the government health centers are free. Anyone who asks for money should be directly challenged and the patient should take the doctors name. They should report this to you as VHT and you report to OmniMed. We will then make sure this is seen to by the District Health Officer Dr. Tumashabe. Remember, VHTs are the voice of the people.

message: Some important messages. This is really important so if you are mentioned make sure you take action as we will be following this up. If you have seen a patient and identified a problem you must give them treatment and follow up to see if it has worked. If it has not worked you must refer them and make sure we know about it. 1. Margaret. A. You saw patient called Mubiru, 30 years old, male on 6th February. They had right sided ear wax. You said you gave olive oil and they needed a washout on saturday. Please confirm when you have done this and the outcome. B. You referred a 53 year old lady who came to see you who had been using antibiotic drops in her right ear. She was seen by us at Seeta nazigo yesterday. She has some hearing loss and some wax in the ear. She needs to be followed up on Friday and assessed to see if she needs a referral to mulago. 2. Kamada. A. You saw a 1 year old boy, kitibwa muwaguzi. He has a left ear drum perforation. We washout and dried. We gave antibiotic ear drops. Dr. Phiona will see him Monday morning at mulago old hospital ent outpatient clinic. Please make sure mum takes him and report back to us the outcome. B. You saw a 5 year old girl with her grandmother yesterday. She needs a follow up on Friday morning with us to see if the antibiotics are making things better. If not she needs a referral to mulago. C. You saw Jessica nansisi a 69 year old lady on 6th february. Her image has been reviewed by Dr. ian. He said it is just wax and itching should settle down over time. Please reassure her. 3. Godfrey. A. You saw the 21 year old girl yesterday with the perforation of the ear drum. We need to follow her up Monday afternoon. All other VHTs keep up your good work.

message: Well done fellow VHTs. Those from places of worship, I welcome you back and safe journey to those who will be going tomorrow. What I don't want that most of you use is speed and commanding. You've turned it into a song. When you move around working in the communities, people will see you and they will come to you. Don't think treating ears is the first thing we have had to do. We have treated lots of diseases and sensitized people on a lot of things. I feel like we have started fighting each other which implies we have got nothing to do. Talking a lot doesn't equate to hard work. Go slow and stop pointing out people's mistakes. May be they didn't intend to do it or meant to say something else. You have changed and have gone so far. This is like the 8th training since we were enrolled as VHTs. We have been with Abigail for sometime but have never got any finger pointing. Why is the pressure so much on this? message: Greetings my fellow VHTs. Those of you from treating patients at the born again church, I welcome you back and thanks for the work you have done. Now personally I have a patient I worked on, went to her place, got to the stage of putting oil in her ears and then gave her an appointment to wash them on Friday. On that day she pretended and went away so I didn't find her there but saw her the following day on Saturday. When I asked her why she was no where to be seen, she said she had gone to Seeta. I told her since she goes to the born again church in makata I would do the ear wash out from there to which she objected. However, much as I saw her today she pretended and went away without me working on her. I am going to give up on her because I don't want to force her. Perhaps she doesn't want her ears treated. Also, there's a message Dr. James sent us saying he will be with us on Monday at the health centre in Seeta but I'm not sure of the time. Those who are aware please let me know so  that I'm in position to keep time. Thanks.

message: I greet you all my fellow VHTs. On this day of 7th March, I would like to thank you all for the work you're doing considering my current situation. Good enough, I may recover. I was told to go back to Wandegeya on Saturday for examination because the doctor wasn't there and I am supposed to go back with shs. 240,000. I have seen all the groups allocated but I haven't seen myself. I thank Dr. James, his colleagues Rebecca, Allan, the two supervisors Margaret and Herbert and all my fellow VHTs. Let me wait for what the doctor will say and then go back after getting the money. I would also like to thank Dr. James for organising another training to ensure we do our work diligently like including the date, showing the affected ear and the specific disease. On Saturday I will be graduating at Kasubi United Christian Life in Kampala. However, we shall host our guests from Makata Sayuni Church. I welcome all fellow VHTs who will be able to attend and celebrate with me. For those who can escort me to Kasubi, the car will pick us at 5am because of jam since the ceremony will be starting at 8am and a lot of people will be graduating. The fee is shs.10,000. Those who won't be able to go, we shall find you at church. Thank you so much. I haven't just declined to work but it's because of the ceremony.

Thank you so much.

message: Good morning my fellow VHTs, according to what Doctor James is asking about, I thought may be he is asking about what we could add on from what we were taught, but I also thought that the people who taught us, are the ones who knew where we stop in what they taught us, so we don't know much details  about ears beyond what we were taught, but what I would like to know is that in my work, I always find patients who have itching in the ears yet we were told not to give anything to that person so my question is, how does such a person get treated? Because some use sticks to itch the ears which may be harmful, another thing is that we get a person who has pain in the ears, and you examine the patient when he/she has nothing that may be causing the pain for example without much wax, but the person says he has pain in the ear, we were taught that such a person should be given pain killers, but we haven't got any training about using pain killers or even getting them, I suggest that if we get trained about those who need pain killers and also understand how long the pain has taken for the person we are giving pain killers. Thank you so much.

message: Greetings my fellow VHTs, Am the usual person greeting you as you know my name, according to me, what we need to know more about is how to use the hook to remove the wax, I humbly request for a training in how to use the hook to remove the wax, because most of the patients I have found, you may give them olive oil and when you are going to washout, you find the wax when it has moved near the ear canal at the entrance which may need to be removed by the hook. I would suggest that we get training about using the hook and after that we get pain killers because truly, people know that the treatment is for free as you know things of Uganda and also a village can not be the same as it is in town, if someone expects that treatment is free and the person comes with a problem with the ears, when the person has pain, and itching, you examine the patient may be you find when the ears are normal but with itching and pain or when they have any abnormalities but sincerely the patient goes back with only olive oil without any pain killers to reduce on the pain and yet you trained us about the pain killers. I request Doctor to add that in our work so that our work can be good instead of someone coming and complaining that I took my ears thinking they are going to help me, I had pain and yet they are telling me to go and buy pain killers for 1000 shillings to relieve the pain. I would suggest that we get the pain killers, or capsules like dicrophenac or panadol, like if we are given a tin of panadol tablets such that a patient can go when he/she has the pain killers and the guidance on how to use them alongside olive oil if they have wax, other than someone saying they examined me but I didn't get any treatment yet I have pain, now like the patient I referred to Allan, up to now he says the ears are still itching, he is using olive oil and he will be washed out tomorrow. Or if there is medicine which can be used to reduce itching in the ear, they should be given to us so that we are sure that we have tackled the problems of ears because you told us that if a person has itching in the ear, leave him or without wax, so shall we leave the person to use sticks because we have no where else to reffer them, I request Doctor James to make that improvement, that's what I think and also my colleagues that I work with. Thank you so muck Allan

message: Thanks for the reply. To answer Herberts point about itching ears. Itching of the ears can be caused by many things. 1. It can actually be caused by putting sticks or cotton buds into the ear... the sticks inflame the ear canal even more and keep the cycle of itching going. 2. It could be the sign of an early skin infection in the ear canal. If the ear canal is very red that might be a sign of infection. 3. It could be caused by a skin problem 4. It could be caused by a lot of wax.

message: Greetings Sarah. Sorry about that problem but as soon as I heard it, I might have got it wrong but my guess was you have an allergy. Personally when I take a walk in coldness especially in the morning, my whole body itches and sometimes my tongue swells. But again you have said your pinna hurts and you experience itching. I think if you feel that way again, you should go for a check up immediately. You never know what kind of disease it could be. I suggest you see someone when you're still feeling like that. message: Greetings Sarah and sorry about that situation. You're not the only one who experiences it. When I travel on a pick up too and I get affected by too much wind, I feel pain in my ears. It feels like piercings inside and around the ear. Compare it to suddenly jumping into water and then you feel pain on your stomach. When you get used to it, the problem ceases to be one. Or if someone pours water on you at once without doing it slowly, you still experience pain. Now the speed of the car is the reason as to why you feel that way but if it's slow, you can't experience it. I don't think there's any other cause.

message: Good morning VHTs. Thanks for the work you are doing. I thank Dr James for caring for us and the care that you are showing for us. The training you promised us from Dr Daniel who is coming from Mbarara and those who are coming on 29th. I request all those who have patients to be seen to inform them so they can be reviewed on that day. Thanks so much supervisor. May god reward you in everything. For caring for us in every way. May god provide you for everything you put your hand in. One more thing I call my upon my fellow VHTs to teach the patients very well. When we talk about oil we don't mean the oil for cars, because someone asked me whether they said can it be any oil e.g. cars, bodas. So the person said I have some oil in my jerry can at home. So I asked them which kind of oil and they said that for bodas. So the patient was wondering if we should use that one. So I told them do not put that in the ear. I told them, we put another kind of oil and we are the only ones to have it and give you directions about how to use it. The one you are talking about can bring harm to the ear. It is not meant for the ear, it is meant for automobiles. I request all the VHTs to inform the people. Tell them exactly what type of oil to use. I wish you a good day but as a reminder we have a meeting at 2pm at the HC today. I request all who have heard to inform a friend.

VHTs and our bosses, I would like your advice. In case one day I kill a snake and then after leave it somewhere, and then the insects eat apart of it but again comeback to my house.  In case those insects get in contact with things that I eat,  is it poisonous? Or if they bite me after eating the snake? Does it affect me? What happens exactly? Please advise me because a lot of people in my village may fall prey. That's my question. I request fellow VHTs, Doctor, Allan, Rebecca please tell me because I personally don't know. Thanks so much. Mulungi is sick with malaria and flue but I gave her treatment. May God be with you.

message: Thanks so much. Sarah your question is so good and it's always good to know something before you get a problem. This is my reply to you. A snake or rather it's body doesn't have any poison but there's a specific place where that poison is. I remember sending you a picture of a woman eating a snake. A lot of people eat snakes like Chinese, Phillipinos and others. Let me look for that photo and send it to your inbox. It means when an insect eats it, it cannot affect you. I think I've replied to your question that insects don't spread venom. Let me send you a photo of the woman eating a snake and she only removed the intestines and the part with poison.

message: Greetings fellow VHTs in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ. Thanks for loving me. Please don't be afraid I'm now okay. But I got so ill yesterday. I was experiencing some piercings right from the legs to the heart. It felt like my heart was getting pulled out and then I would lose energy. I couldn't even speak. But due to people's prayers, I'm now okay. When I got to the health centre, the doctors didn't know where to start from so they referred me. They had no idea what the condition was after explaining it to them. I will be fine only that we got a boda boda accident on our way. It bounced after knocking something and we fell to the other side so I ended up hitting my chest and hand. My hand got some injuries. Anyway the first serious condition is not there anymore but I'm paralyzed now. I can't feel any pain.

message: About the other issue of milk in the ear, the milk they are talking about does not drop direct in the ear, for us in Buganda, the milk can drop on the knees when the mother is breastfeeding the baby, that is when people say that the baby got some milk drops in the ear, that is an infection that started long time ago, but in our tradition we have people who treat this, (traditional healers) but when we go to the doctors they say its pus but it is an infection in most cases a child is born with it. Have a good night am Johnson Wadda
anonymisedMessageWithPseudonymReplacemen: About the other issue of milk in the ear, the milk they are talking about does not drop direct in the ear, for us in Buganda, the milk can drop on the knees when the mother is breastfeeding the baby, that is when people say that the baby got some milk drops in the ear, that is an infection that started long time ago, but in our tradition we have people who treat this, (traditional healers) but when we go to the doctors they say its pus but it is an infection in most cases a child is born with it. undefined: Sharing cultural beliefs about ear disease - Matthew is one of the older VHTs and he has a lot of cultural knowledge about local traditions.

message: Still on the same issue, because this issue is so important, for us in Buganda we have traditional doctors who treat such an infection which can't be treated by other qualified Doctors, we have diseases which can't even be treated by white doctors  but when you use the traditional medicine you get healed, we have seen this for a long time but for us keep referring to medical doctors (bazungu) but we also have the medicine that heals that problem, it is an illness which sometimes fails to be healed by the qualified Doctors then they end up saying someone's ear has rotten yet it is an illness. That is my second explanation about this issue.

message: Greetings all VHTs who work with me.  Also thank you so so much for participating in answering the questions. Let us get something to learn from, let there not be someone who gets annoyed about other VHTs answers. If that person is wrong, let us just lean and not be upset at what others say, even if it isn't correct. Also as we are told - let us read the books given to us. All the information is there. If we take our time to read and ask questions, we will learn the proper treatment for our community and our patients. Now, I also want to encourage you that tomorrow, let us try as hard as possible. I know we might not know the exact problems people get, but whoever gets an issue let the supervisors know in time such that we can make a plan. We now know we won't be with Sarah, but others let me know if there is a problem for our meeting. I also request you friends , let us be around tomorow. Let us be there at the health centre for 10am-3pm. I beg you - for the goodness of the project. Let us be around for the meeting with Dr. James. I wish you a good night, but all in all let us try keep up our effort. We don't want to get there and they ask 'why isn't this so and so coming'. I just request you to be around. Good night. I love you all.

Covering her - feeding her and also giving her body building foods that can't be affected with the disease so the white blood cells can get more energy. That is my suggestion and idea and that is what I tell the mother. To give body building foods, beans, mukene (silver fish), soya, so that the body can have more energy and also that WBCs can be stronger. Thanks alot good night. I am your VHT Wadda Johnson, Makata.

message: Good morning ladies and gentlemen. Thanks for all the work you're doing. Today I want to talk to you about the issue of the files. I would like us to work together whether one received a file or not. The reason I am saying that is because some people received files with people they didn't treat or who don't stay in their areas. If someone sends a name of a person from their file that they didn't treat or who don't stay in their area, the one who knows them should help and direct that person. Today someone else may be having a file but next time it will be you. I suggest we work together to make this work easy because it's 30th and almost June. It will be bad if we look for those people without finding them yet someone who could be knowing them just didn't let us know. An example is yesterday when Herbert asked who knew the patients he listed down. I am not sure if you sent him a private message because I haven't seen anyone directing him. I therefore suggest we work together so we can finish the work that was given to us. This is not about only those who got the file but everyone. I will be happy if we help each other and do this work very fast.

message: Greetings fellow health workers. I am announcing the death of our grandchild called Nyonyintono. He disappeared on Monday and was never seen again until today when he was found dead in Nakabugo, where he happens to have been killed from at a brick laying area. His motorcycle was stolen too. He had gone to see his sick sibling but then his other elder sibling requested him to drive him to Namubiru and since then he disappeared. He was found dead today so his dead body has been taken to Mulago where it will be for the rest of the night. We shall bury him here tomorrow at my in-law's place Mayinja in Kirijja at 2:00pm. That's it. May God bless you.
